# CODEOWNERS intentionally has no active path rules.
#
# GitHub auto-requests review from CODEOWNERS on every PR touching
# matching paths, even when `require_code_owner_reviews` is disabled
# in branch protection. For a solo + automation-driven project, that
# created notification noise on every mechanical version-sync PR.
#
# Protection now comes from branch protection status checks: allowlist
# (repo-structure.yml), public-hygiene, secret-scan. Those gate merges
# without pinging a human.
#
# When contributors arrive, reintroduce specific owner rules here.
